cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.EM, cs.SY, cs.LG 

The paper discusses the use of physical systems for implementing reservoir computing, which is a subfield of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also mentions the use of different physical substrates and devices, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) and cs.EM (Electromagnetics). The discussion of hardware implementation and practical applications suggests that it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
